  "mismatches": [
    "Docs describe filter.query as a keyword filter, but every tested value (including nonsense strings) produced identical totals and rows, implying the implementation ignores the parameter."
  ],
  "gaps": [
    "Still unclear what backend fields filter.query is intended to search; it produced no effect in any probe."
  ],
  "risks": [
    "Consumers expecting server-side keyword filtering may need to implement client filtering until the query parameter behavior is clarified.",
    "Clients must handle totals and row fields that switch between null and numeric based on spending_type to avoid type errors.",
    "Pagination inputs must be coerced to integers; decimal or out-of-range values surface 400/422 errors that callers must catch."
  ]
